$ Vim - indenting text

{ Methods

  Four methods, ordered from rudimentary to most flexible:
    • → development/vim/options/autoindent[autoindent]
    • → development/vim/options/smartindent[smartindent]
    • → development/vim/options/cindent[cindent]
    • → development/vim/options/indentexpr[indentexpr] (which seems to be set indirectly via → development/vim/commands/filetype#vim-filetype-indent-on[`:filetype indent on`])

  The more flexible overrides the more rudimentary if multiple methods are »enabled«.

}
{ Options

  Options that are relevant in conjunction with indenting text:
    • `autoindent`
    • `cindent`
    • `expandtab`
    • `indentexpr`
    • `indentkeys`
    • `shiftwidth`
    • `softtabstop`
    • `smarttab`
    • `tabstop`

}

sa:
  `:help indent.txt`

  → development/vim/options/indentkeys

  → development/vim/runtime/indent,
  -
  → development/vim/runtime/indent_vim

  → development/vim/editing/tricks[Editing tricks]
